{"id":64393,"date":"2021-10-02T13:36:11","date_gmt":"2021-10-02T12:36:11","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=64393"},"modified":"2022-04-09T09:31:29","modified_gmt":"2022-04-09T08:31:29","slug":"elsa-trail-tuscany-diborrato-waterfall","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/italy\/elsa-trail-tuscany-diborrato-waterfall\/","title":{"rendered":"Exploring the Elsa Trail and Diborrato Waterfall in Tuscany"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-about-elsa-trail-sentierelsa\">About Elsa Trail (Sentierelsa)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Sentierelsa is a beautiful walking path in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/italy\/tuscany\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Tuscany<\/a> that allows you to follow the river for a few kilometers. The path starts at Spugna Bridge (Ponte di Spugna), which is located in the village Colle di Val d&#x2019;Elsa. It reaches all the way to Diborrato waterfall and the San Marziale bridge. The trail is characterized by small stone-step river crossings, wooden bridges, small waterfalls, and a very pleasant natural shade from the trees.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--tip \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--tip\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Good to know:<\/strong> There are no toilets or changing rooms at the Elsa Trail.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1.jpg\" alt=\"Elsa Trail waterfall tuscany italy\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Elsa Trail waterfall tuscany italy\" class=\"wp-image-64414 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1281px) 100vw, 1281px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1.jpg 1281w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-226x338.jpg 226w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-20x30.jpg 20w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-109x163.jpg 109w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-120x180.jpg 120w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-512x768.jpg 512w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-683x1024.jpg 683w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-721x1080.jpg 721w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-961x1440.jpg 961w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-300x450.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-600x899.jpg 600w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1-20x30.jpg\" src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092047\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-1.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>A round trip to the waterfall and back is about 5 kilometers (2 hours of walking). We recommend spending an hour or so at the waterfall so you can expect to spend an entire morning or afternoon at the Elsa Trail.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The trail along the river with silky blue waters has some similarities with the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/laos\/luang-prabang\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Kuang Si Falls in Luang Prabang, Laos<\/a>.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02110231\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-6-568x810.jpg\" alt=\"\"><\/noscript><img width=\"237\" height=\"338\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-64425 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02110231\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-6-568x810.jpg 568w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02110231\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-6-421x600.jpg 421w, https:\/\/static.