k.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02110254\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-8-540x810.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"h-hiking-the-elsa-trail-diborrato-waterfall\">Hiking the Elsa Trail &amp; Diborrato Waterfall<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Elsa Trail, which leads to the Diborrato Waterfall has two entry points: From the <a href=\"https:\/\/goo.gl\/maps\/efUwXJ6ecpiZZuPF8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Spugna<\/a> or <a href=\"https:\/\/goo.gl\/maps\/KyiWCdxYVVyDfpXY6\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">San Marziale Bridge<\/a>. On both bridges is a path indicated with signs leading the path of the Elsa Trail. (Sentierelsa) The trail has a total length of 2.5 kilometers one-way with scenic bridges and river crossings. Expect to spend half a day at this site.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092130\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-5.jpg\" alt=\"Elsa Trail waterfall tuscany italy\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"300\" alt=\"Elsa Trail waterfall tuscany italy\" class=\"wp-image-64422 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092130\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-5.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/02092130\/Elsa-Trail-waterfall-tuscany-italy-5-800x534.jpg 